ne x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>如果我是新加坡政府，我的目标是修建更多这样的街道。如果他们有能力以零虫子的方式将城市覆盖在修剪整齐的绿色植物中，他们就有能力打造对行人来说更加舒适的街道。</p><p>不管怎样，抛开远足，如果你还没有的话，你绝对应该去新加坡看看。惊人的财富和未来主义的太阳朋克建筑只是其中的两个景点——还有美味的食物、有趣的民族社区、美丽的景色、有趣的历史和相当壮观的多样化建筑风格。</p><p>记住不要不小心带任何大麻，否则他们会<a href="https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/up-to-30-years-jail-for-possession-of-cannabis-with-roll-out-of-stricter-drug-laws-from-june">用拐杖打你，然后把你送进监狱几十年</a>。 </p><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?"><span>现在订阅</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/singapore-urbanism?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"> <a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/singapore-urbanism?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>分享</span></a></p>; 
Yes, it's possible to imagine progressive dystopias We shouldn't just worry about the means of progress, but the ends as well. https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/yes-its-possible-to-imagine-progressive https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/yes-ts-possible-to-imagine-progressionsNoah Smith Fri, 10 Nov 2023 07:52:40 GMT <div class="captioned-image-container"><figure> <a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg" width="722" height="481.3333333333333" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/c8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:624,&quot;width&quot;:936,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:722,&quot;bytes&quot;:135733,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture></div></a> <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line><figcaption class="image-caption"> <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/53301297@N00">PASA47</a> ， <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/?ref=openverse">CC</a>的“<a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/53301297@N00/14486751845">唯一可持续增长是降解</a>”。</figcaption></figure></div><p>最近，一个想法一直在na。几个月前，布拉德·德隆（Brad DeLong）和我<a href="https://braddelong.substack.com/p/podcast-hexapodia-liii-rule-1-no#details">进行了一个播客</a>，在那里我们讨论了像布莱恩娜·吴（Brianna Wu），马特·伊格莱西亚斯（Matt Yglesias）和埃兹拉·克莱因（Ezra Klein）这样的中心左派人物，他们向左边的一些人推回了一些人。布拉德（Brad）从根本上讲这些推动力是关于<em>战术</em>的 - 正如他所看到的那样，布莱恩娜（Brianna），马特（Matt）和埃兹拉（Ezra）对某些进步主义者在尝试实现乌托邦的尝试并争辩采取更务实，有效的方法感到沮丧。这是漫长的传统的一部分，在这种传统中，倡导社会变革的激进主义者争论社会准备的变化。</p><p>但是，尽管我确实认为有些事情正在进行，但我不同意布拉德（Brad），这主要是倒退的目的。取而代之的是，我认为我们真正看到的是对进步主义者似乎正在为之奋斗的某些<em>目标</em>越来越不适，而不是关于变革的步伐，而是关于它的方向。当布拉德（Brad）挑战我列出反乌托邦渐进式愿景的一些例子时，我立即说了“降解”，他同意了。</p><p>无论如何，请注意我说“一些”一词。我想要的事情是许多进步的愿景，例如更大的经济平等，种族财富差距的缩小以及气候变化的逆转！如果您将这篇文章解释为说进步主义的<em>书面大型</em>项目是一个反乌托邦的项目，那么您将严重地误解了我。我也不是说保守主义比进步主义更好，或者政治权利不包含反乌托邦的视野。确实如此。</p><p>取而代之的是，我要说的是，在2010年代令人震惊的匆忙中所接受的一些大想法被误导了，应该被丢弃，以便为人类实际上想要生活的乌托邦努力。</p><p>这是四种此类愿景的列表。</p><h4>降解</h4><p>当然，这是布拉德问题的简单答案。我写了多篇文章，详细介绍了为什么停止或逆转经济增长（过去十年中一些渐进界变得时尚的想法）是不可行的，也是不受欢迎的，这是限制人类环境影响的一种方式。首先，我认为，降解所需的生活水平的下降使其成为政治上的非标准，而所涉及的全球中央规划数量将无法实施： </p><div class="digest-post-embed" data-attrs="{&quot;nodeId&quot;:&quot;52bf6b2d-b886-46cf-8a98-7325f073a207&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;I was going to write a lengthy post explaining why &#8220;degrowth&#8221; &#8212; the idea that we need to halt economic growth in order to save the planet &#8212; is a very bad idea. But in the meantime, other people have written that post, or recorded that podcast, and done it well. These include&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:&quot;sm&quot;,&quot;isEditorNode&quot;:true,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;People are realizing that degrowth is bad&quot;,&quot;publishedBylines&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:8243895,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith&quot;,&quot;bio&quot;:&quot;Econ blogger&quot;,&quot;photo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/89fd964a-586f-461a-9f5a-ea4587d45728_397x441.png&quot;,&quot;is_guest&quot;:false,&quot;bestseller_tier&quot;:10000}],&quot;post_date&quot;:&quot;2021-09-06T08:40:54.095Z&quot;,&quot;cover_image&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Faeddab2a-6c56-4e5b-9c35-9ca0fecd86bd_1024x682.jpeg&quot;,&quot;cover_image_alt&quot;:null,&quot;canonical_url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/people-are-realizing-that-degrowth&quot;,&quot;section_name&quot;:null,&quot;id&quot;:39760555,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;newsletter&quot;,&quot;reaction_count&quot;:129,&quot;comment_count&quot;:106,&quot;publication_name&quot;:&quot;Noahpinion&quot;,&quot;publication_logo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04281755-2cd6-42e5-a496-e69153abebb2_281x281.png&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false}"></div><p>我还认为，解决气候变化需要增长，因为用太阳能和风能和电池代替我们的能源需要<em>大量</em>的经济产出。然后，一旦我们改用了这些能源，它们将变得如此便宜（由于学习曲线），我们实际上将比以前更高的消费更高。</p><p>在后续文章中，我批评了降解思想的研究和言论，这通常是基于意识形态动机的伪科学： </p><div class="digest-post-embed" data-attrs="{&quot;nodeId&quot;:&quot;15f58e2c-0355-411d-a35f-7e2969e03f23&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;A year and a half ago, I wrote a post entitled &#8220;People are realizing that degrowth is bad&#8221;. Around that time, the degrowth movement had started to receive a bit of attention in the U.S., as part of the general push for major action on climate change. But writers like&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:&quot;sm&quot;,&quot;isEditorNode&quot;:true,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Degrowth: We can't let it happen here!&quot;,&quot;publishedBylines&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:8243895,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith&quot;,&quot;bio&quot;:&quot;Econ blogger&quot;,&quot;photo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/89fd964a-586f-461a-9f5a-ea4587d45728_397x441.png&quot;,&quot;is_guest&quot;:false,&quot;bestseller_tier&quot;:10000}],&quot;post_date&quot;:&quot;2023-05-24T01:54:00.942Z&quot;,&quot;cover_image&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F058020be-b262-4c24-88c2-ba3e1c8e0184_1024x681.jpeg&quot;,&quot;cover_image_alt&quot;:null,&quot;canonical_url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/degrowth-we-cant-let-it-happen-here&quot;,&quot;section_name&quot;:null,&quot;id&quot;:123140587,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;newsletter&quot;,&quot;reaction_count&quot;:201,&quot;comment_count&quot;:80,&quot;publication_name&quot;:&quot;Noahpinion&quot;,&quot;publication_logo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04281755-2cd6-42e5-a496-e69153abebb2_281x281.png&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true}"></div><p>正如我在第二篇文章中所解释的那样，我将脱生物视为试图使民族衰落的尝试，这就是为什么这个想法在欧洲比美国更受欢迎的原因</p><p>我不想击败这一点，但我认为重要的是要强调未来的不愉快和不人道的未来。富裕国家的人们将被迫接受较低的生活水平，而发展中国家的人们将拥有<a href="https://brankomilanovic.substack.com/p/degrowth-solving-the-impasse-by-magical">更加微薄的未来</a>。这种情况无疑会引起怨恨，导致对授权大规模贫困的领导人的反对。在推翻降解政权之后，我们将摆动完全倾向于承诺无限资源消耗的领导者，这时环境将比以前更糟。这是一个事实，即降解将使投资绿色能源和保护环境的其他技术变得更加困难。</p><p>因此，尽管我认为我们确实需要担心增长的潜在负面后果并尽力减轻这些危害，但我认为试图使自己贫穷以拯救环境会成为我们和环境的灾难性错误。这不是任何进步的争取的事情。</p><h4>驱逐“殖民者”</h4><p>在我出生时，非殖民化的非殖民化（即，国家都从其欧洲帝国霸主获得独立的国家就已经有效地完成了。无论从道德和<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/against-hickelism">经济上来说</a>，这对世界来说都是一件非常好的事情。但是近年来，美国一些进步主义者开始谈论一种完全不同类型的“非殖民化”，这是从其祖先定居的地区驱逐“定居者殖民地”人口。</p><p> “非殖民化”的另一种含义一直在人文学术界和一些左倾的媒体和激进主义运动中越来越受欢迎，但在哈马斯于10月7日对以色列袭击以色列之后，它爆炸到了国家舞台上。在哈马斯的屠杀和强奸狂欢之后，青少年时尚作家纳吉玛·谢里夫（Najma Sharif）发布了以下推文： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1be80b0a-b5a2-4898-a77d-4fd80df00a22_375x134.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubst