"100vw"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>我记得被此图形说服了；并不是因为我认为假设的入侵计划看起来特别合理，而是因为这使我对纳粹德国和帝国日本的占领在接管了世界其他大部分地区之后是否会离开美国。他们似乎不太可能拥有。</p><p>但是，在那个时代的政府传播方面，为美国在第二次世界大战中发挥作用的电影只是冰山一角。罗斯福政府建立了整个战争信息办公室，该<a href="https://www.politico.com/story/2011/06/roosevelt-creates-office-of-war-information-june-13-1942-056772">办公室试图说服该国</a>美国的基本团结和自由价值的首要地位。还有无数其他这样的有说服力的努力，例如著名的海报，这些海报试图说服恐惧的美国人信任他们的非白人和共产主义盟友。 </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F86b968e7-f1b3-44ab-b2f4-05e3a87f2db8_560x777.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F86b968e7-f1b3-44ab-b2f4-05e3a87f2db8_560x777.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F86b968e7-f1b3-44ab-b2f4-05e3a87f2db8_560x777.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F86b968e7-f1b3-44ab-b2f4-05e3a87f2db8_560x777.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2